<html><head><title>SBSC Issues:  Minimum Wage</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><h2>Minimum Wage</h2><hr width="45%" size="4">
<p></center>
Congress is once again considering a minimum wage hike.  The Senate recently approved a procedural motion that will bring a minimum wage increase vote within the next several months. The minimum wage, which is politically popular, is most harmful to small businesses.  Most employers pay above the minimum wage, and many determine wages according to the minimum wage.  Thus an increase in the minimum wage will have a ripple effect on the wages paid by businesses - many small firms simply cannot absorb such a budget impact.  
<P><i>See Grant Maloy's testimony "<a href="/sbsc/ct2-22-5.html">President Clinton's Proposal to Increase the Minimum Wage</a>" for more information.</i>
<P>
Send a letter to the following Senators and Congressman expressing your opposition to an increase of the minimum wage:<p>

<a href="/sbsc/l-minwag-gephardt.html">Minority Leader Richard Gephardt</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-minwag-daschle.html">Minority Leader Tom Daschle</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-minwag-ford.html">Minority Whip Wendell Ford</a><p>

You can also print out a letter to send to your <a href="/sbsc/l-minwag-congress.txt">Congressman</a> or <a href="/sbsc/l-minwag-senate.txt">Senator</a>.<p>
<br>
