<h1>Edwin Meese</h1>
<p>Ive admired over the years the fine work that the Foundation has done, in terms of its college campus work... its support of student activities, these national conferences during the summer, and the many other things that they do to bring conservatives to campuses, providing an opportunity to balance the debate.  On most of our campuses you dont always have the opportunity to have conservative speakers as readily as people representing other points of view.  What the Foundation does to balance that out, even it up, is certainly a very important thing.</p>
</body>
