and shrink workers' pay.
<P>
<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This process usually works by delaying,
reducing, or canceling wage increases. In most years, additional
investment and training increase worker productivity, making employees
more valuable and allowing businesses to increases wages. When
these productivity increases are accompanied by higher taxes,
however, it is government, not the workers, that captures all
the benefits.
