<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Outrage du Jour</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<img src="/nationalreview/images/outrage.gif" ALT="Outrage du Jour">
<br>
<br>


<HR width=50%> 
<!-----------------Townhall------------------------------>
<I>February 1, 1997</I></center>
<BR>
<BR>

<P><center>
<H2>Right To Lie</H2><br>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>




"I am opposed to abortion and to government funding of abortions."
Bill Clinton, September 26, 1986 letter to Arkansas Right to Life 
<P>
"I have always believed that the decision to have an abortion generally should be between a woman, her doctor, her conscience, and her God."
Clinton's veto message on the Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act, April 11, 1996

<P>
(Flip-flop courtesy of <I>Human Events</I>, January 24, 1997)

</blockquote>
