<title>The Washington Watch: The Daily Radio Commentary Station List</title>
<body>
<center><h2>The Daily Radio Commentary Station List</h2></center><p>
What's the best way for your family to stay informed about the national
 policies and trends that affect your family most?  Listen to <B>Washington
 Watch</B>, <a href="/townhall/FRC/whois/bauer.html">Gary Bauer's</a> 
daily radio commentary.  Now available, every day, on
 over 140 stations across the land.  Former Under Secretary of Education, White 
House Domestic Policy Adviser, and now President of the Family Research Council, 
Bauer combines conviction and common sense in 90 seconds of insightful commentary. 
<p>
Recent editions of <B>Gary Bauer's Washington Watch</B> have discussed such topics 
as the Clinton Administration's flip-flops on child pornography, the new national 
education standards' neglect of American heroes, and pro-family tax relief.  
<p>
Click on your state on the map below to check the listings for a station near you. 
Otherwise, you can take a look at the <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/station.html">whole
 list.</a></font> If your local station doesn't 
carry <B>Gary Bauer's Washington Watch</B>, drop them a line and tell them this 
is a feature <i>your family</i> wants to hear.<p>
