<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - February 6, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
February 6, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

This week the White House thought it would be a good idea to
make Bill Clinton look like a forward-thinking leader by focusing
on education.  But instead they exposed his belief in big government.

<p>

Keep in mind that this is the same president, who just last year
declared the era of big government was over.  Now he's launching
a $51 billion initiative that would massively expand the federal
role in education.  Now that may sound good, but the facts tell
a different story.  In the past 18 years since the creation of
the Department of Education, test scores have gone down, the quality
of education has declined and too many schools have become unsafe
for students and teachers alike.  You know all this already, of
course.  All this despite a tripling of its budget.  Now the president
is calling for a 20% increase.

<p>

That's exactly the wrong direction to take.  There's no connection
between government spending and educational improvement.  But
there is a connection between government spending and government
control.  This administration should look for ways to increase
parent's control instead of government's.  It's the only way we
can really reform education.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

<center><b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwold.html.cgi#current">Last Month's Commentaries</a>] 
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwdaily.html.cgi#current">This Month's Commentaries</a>]
</b></center>

<p>

