<p>

<center><h2>LOOKING FOR PRO-FAMILY RESPONSE TO<br>
THE DNC CONVENTION?<br>
CALL 1-800-236-8538</h2></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> Live from Washington, D.C., <b>Gary
L. Bauer</b> -- Family Research Council president and domestic
policy adviser to Ronald Reagan -- will be available for comment
as the Democratic National Convention takes to the airways August
26 to 29.

<p>

Also available, FRC's Deputy Director of Government Relations
Cathy Deeds in Chicago for comment or analysis.

<p>

If you're interested in pro-family tax relief, welfare reform,
life issues, cultural decay, the growing drug abuse problem or
any of the gambit of issues covered by the domestic policy label,
call either <B>202-393-2100</B> or <B>1-800-236-8538</B>.

<p>

For a copy of the <I>Whole Family Catalogue of Pro-Family Platform
Planks</I> or other information or interviews, call the FRC media
office.

