<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Mackinac Center Offers Freedom From Bad Labor
Advice</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">This resource from the Mackinac
Center gives workers straight answers to common questions about
labor unions and employee rights and responsibilities. The question-and-answer
format helps workers understand how federal labor law affects
them directly on topics including mandatory union membership and
payment dues. Public employees, including teachers, will also
benefit from this brochure.  CONTACT: Mackinac Center for Public
Policy, 119 Ashman Street, P.O. Box 568, Midland, MI 48640, 517/631-0900,
fax 517/631-0964. <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Fund to Take Back Texas Prisons, Inc. Established</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The Fund to Take Back Texas
Prisons, Inc., has been created to end the Federal Judiciary's
contol over Texas prisons by restoring state sovereignty for Texas
and all 50 states under the 10th amendment to the U.S. Constitution.
CONTACT: The Fund to Take Back Texas Prisons, Inc., 1500 So. Dairy
Ashford, Suite 115, Houston, TX 77077.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>Washington Institute For Policy Studies Establishes
Web Site</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">The Washington Institute for
Policy Studies (WIPS) has established a web site on the Internet
at the address: http://www.wips.org. The homepage features an
&quot;Institute Spotlight&quot; which focuses on their latest
publication or event. It will also include: a John Carlson home
page; the latest issues of <I>Counterpoint</I>; listing of staff,
board of directors and board advisors; and a publications and
policy page. CONTACT: Washington Institute for Policy Studies,
P.O. Box 24645, Seattle, WA 98124, 206/938-6300, fax 206/938-6313,
e-mail <a href="mailto:wips@wips.org">wips@wips.org</a>, Internet <a href="http://www.wips.org">http://www.wips.org</a><BR>
</FONT>
