has published its fifth anniversary issue of its bimonthly newsletter
<I>Liberty &amp; Law</I>. This issue includes a look back at the
highlights of The Institute for Justice's first five years, inlcuding
profiles of IJ clients in important cases. Also included is a
summary of IJ's school choice agenda. CONTACT: Institute for Justice,
1717 Pennslyvania Avenue, N.W., Suite 200, Washington, D.C. 20006,
202/955-1300, fax 202/955-1329, e-mail <a href="mailto:general@instituteforjustice.org">general@instituteforjustice.org</a>
 Internet <a href="http://www.instituteforjustice.org">http://www.instituteforjustice.org</a><BR>
